	that last one took almost two weeks to find.  I went down to 5.0 from 5.1 and all of a sudden we're back in business

	virtualbox provides you a platform on which to run.  vagrant is used to configure a virtual machine on virtualbox and i believe homestead is a laravel app that configures the laravel/machine the way it needs to and passes that off to vagrant.

